  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou1-noncannulated-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against a required level 3; this shortfall is accepted because the COU is explicitly scoped to static compression-bending under a single ASTM F1717 protocol, and the regulatory decision does not require dynamic or fatigue loading validation at this stage. Quantitative validation metric E/uval is below 1.96 for all QoI comparisons across both laboratories. The FEA ensemble approach across three independent codes provides additional epistemic robustness. Overall credibility is sufficient for a Medium model risk, Medium decision consequence COU. Package accepted.",
